         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Contract for the Provision of Services Relating to the Role of Licensee Microgeneration Certification Scheme to the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Climate Change.</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>TRN 1381/11/2017</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="75100000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>BEIS needs to have a contingency in place for a one month contract extension for the continuation of the current services provided by Gemserv as the administrator of the Microgeneration certification scheme (MCS). While it is expected that novation will occur in April, there is the potential for unforeseen delays to result in the novation of the scheme to the MCS Charitable foundation taking place after the current contract completes on 30.4.2018.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">72100</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>United Kingdom.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>This notice covers the contingency for a one month contract extension for the continuation of the current services provided by Gemserv as the administrator of the Microgeneration certification scheme (MCS), for the potential case of any unforeseen delays to the novation (making independent of government) of the scheme. The extension would cover the period from 1.5.2018 to 31.5.2018 but will only be awarded if the novation date is delayed until after 30.4.2018. 2 government incentive schemes (Feed-in tariff scheme, Renewable heat incentive) and the microgeneration industry rely on the functioning of MCS to develop and maintain standards, certify installers and installations in accordance with standards, to provide assurance to consumers and help the growth of the renewable microgeneration sector.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>Germserv provide administration of the MCS which includes the following deliverables:</P>
                  <P>— financial administration,</P>
                  <P>— license services,</P>
                  <P>— database and website maintenance,</P>
                  <P>— database services,</P>
                  <P>— help desk,</P>
                  <P>— secretariat function (Working groups, Management panel, Steering group),</P>
                  <P>— and reporting.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
                  <D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE/>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The Department for business, energy and industrial strategy is in the process of novating (making independent of government) the MCS to the MCS Charitable foundation. Following novation, BEIS will no longer be responsible for contracting the delivery body for the scheme. However, there is a need for a contingency one month extension for the potential case of any unforeseen delays to novation. If novation occurs before the end of the current contract on 30.4.2018 as expected, the one month extension will not be needed. The modification does not alter the overall nature of the contract and the increase in price does not exceed 50 % of the value of the original contract and the following three month extension.</P>
                     <P>Given that the current contract ends on 30.4.2018, the department needs to have a contingency in place to ensure the continuous functioning of the scheme to support two government incentives (Renewable Heat Incentive, Feed in Tariff), consumers, and the industry while novation is finalised. A Voluntary ex ante transparency notice was published on 23.11.2017 — publication number 2017/S 225-469218 for a 3 month contract to expire on 30th April, this new VEAT is purely as a contingency of any slight delay, should it be required, to ensure business as usual.</P>
                     <P>We are claiming this extension against the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 — clause 72 (1) (c) (i),(ii) and (iii).</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
